# FileSizeGuard allowlist — pre-existing NFR-FOR-D4 debt captured at phase-0.
#
# SPEC DIVERGENCE (approved 2026-04-11):
# TASK-AGS-002 §"Allowlist starter content: exactly one entry, src/main.rs"
# was written under the assumption that main.rs was the sole >500-line file.
# Phase-0 baseline execution discovered 67 additional offenders across 11
# crates. Steven explicitly approved adding all 67 to this allowlist to
# preserve the guard's forward-looking purpose: catch NEW >500-line files
# while phases 4+ progressively refactor existing debt. The guard's intent
# (NFR-FOR-D4-MAINTAINABILITY) is preserved even though the starter-content
# clause is relaxed.
#
# The allowlist SHRINKS over time. Every phase-N task that refactors a file
# below 500 lines MUST remove its entry here in the same commit.
#
# Format: repo-relative path, one per line. Lines starting with '#' and
# blank lines are ignored. Grouped by crate for review-friendliness.

